<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Scop." class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Kali" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kali tragus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tragus">Kali tragus (L.) Scop.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
This species was observed and photographed on a sandstone outcrop approximately 1 km northeast of MDRS on September 20, 2015 (Fig. 25), however this plant was not collected due to time and equipment constraints. Common on sandy plateaus and 
<taxonomicName genus="Guterriezia" lsidName="Guterriezia" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="genus">Guterriezia</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Bromus</taxonomicName>
dominated scrub near MDRS, this species is a noxious weed found throughout the southwestern United States (
<bibRefCitation author="Welsh, S. L." journalOrPublisher="Print Services, Brigham Young University, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="A Utah Flora" year="1993">Welsh et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
). This species was previously reported for the nearby San Rafael Swell (
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris 1983</bibRefCitation>
) as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Salsola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salsola iberica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="iberica">Salsola iberica</taxonomicName>
Sennen &amp; Pau, which was later synonymized under 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Salsola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salsola tragus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tragus">Salsola tragus</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Mosyakin, SL" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="2003">Mosyakin 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Further phylogenetic work has transferred this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Kali" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kali" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Kali</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Akhani, H" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Plant Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="931 - 956" title="Diversification of the old world Salsolae s. l. (Chenopodiaceae): molecular phylogenetic analysis of nuclear and chloroplast data sets and a revised classification" volume="168" year="2007">Akhani et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), now placed in the expanded 
<taxonomicName family="Amaranthaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="APG III," journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="105 - 121" title="An update of the Angiosperm Phylogeny Group classification for the orders and families of flowering plants: APG III" volume="161" year="2009">APG III 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
